====Comebacks/game-winning drives in the fourth quarter/overtime====
Roethlisberger set a NFL rookie record in 2004 with five comeback wins in the fourth quarter, and six game-winning drives in the fourth quarter/overtime (including one playoff game).<ref>[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/tiny/nOrha "Player Game Finder Query Results"] Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref><ref>[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/tiny/Uw115 "Player Game Finder Query Results"] Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref> Roethlisberger has the most comeback wins (19) and game-winning drives (25) through the first seven seasons of a player's career.<ref>[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/tiny/xq7Ev "Player Game Finder Query Results"] Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref><ref>[http://pfref.com/tiny/DJex9 "Player Game Finder Query Results"] Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref>

