===NFL records===
*Most regular season wins in a season, rookie QB &mdash; 13 (2004) <ref>[http://www.usatoday.com/sports/football/nfl/steelers/2005-01-11-big-ben-cover_x.htm "Rookie Roethlisberger wins over everybody"], USA Today</ref>
*Longest regular season win streak to start a career for a NFL QB &mdash; 15 games (won all 13 starts in the 2004 season, won first 2 games of the 2005 season)<ref name="Ben Roethlisberger Profile">[http://www.steelers.com/team/player/49181/ "Ben Roethlisberger Profile"], Steelers.com</ref>
*Most wins as a starting quarterback in first five NFL seasons (reg. season only) - 51 (from 2004<U+2013>2008)<ref name="dallasnews.com" />
*Highest passer rating, rookie season &mdash; 98.1 (2004)<ref name="NFL Records - Passing">[http://www.nfl.com/history/randf/records/indiv/passing "NFL Records - Passing"] NFL.com</ref>
*Highest completion percentage, rookie season &mdash; 66.4% (2004)<ref name="NFL Records - Passing" />
*Highest single-game completion percentage, rookie season (min. 20 attempts) &mdash; 84.0% (completed 21/25 passes at Dallas on 10/17/2004)<ref>[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/tiny/uednB "Player Game Finder Query Results"] Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref>
*Most games with a completion percentage of 70.0% or higher, rookie season (min. 10 attempts) &mdash; 6 (2004)<ref>[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/tiny/mxY5c "Player Game Finder Query Results"] Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref>
*Most games with a completion percentage of 80.0% or higher, single season (min. 10 attempts) &mdash; 4 (2007)<ref>[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/play-index/tiny/snwgX "Player Game Finder Query Results"] Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref>
*(Tie) Most touchdown passes, [[Monday Night Football]] game &mdash; 5 (11/5/2007 vs. Baltimore Ravens) <ref name="Ben Roethlisberger Profile" />
*First QB to start two [[AFC Championship Game|Conference Championship]] games in first two seasons in the NFL (2004 & 2005)<ref name="Ben Roethlisberger Profile" />
*Youngest starting QB ever to win the Super Bowl (2005; second-youngest QB to play in the Super Bowl, behind [[Dan Marino]])<ref>[http://www.usatoday.com/sports/football/nfl/steelers/2006-02-02-roethlisberger-cover_x.htm "Steelers' Roethlisberger a perfect fit for Super Bowl XL"], USA Today</ref>
*Second quarterback in NFL history, along with Peyton Manning, to register three perfect passing games during the regular season, and the only quarterback to ever register two perfect passing games in one regular season.<ref name="Ben Roethlisberger Profile" />
*Lowest passer rating for a Super Bowl winning QB &mdash; 22.6 (Completed 9 of 21 passes for zero touchdowns with two interceptions)<ref>[http://www.usatoday.com/sports/football/nfl/steelers/2006-10-12-steelers-cover_x.htm "Roethlisberger, defending Super Bowl champs Steelers stumble to 1-3 start"], USA Today</ref>
*Tied for most seasons with one or more postseason starts in the first five years in the league since 1960, with four starts (tied with [[Bernie Kosar]], [[Donovan McNabb]], and Eli Manning).<ref>Stat given during the game on 01/11/2009 vs. the Chargers., CBS Sports</ref>

===Pittsburgh Steelers franchise records===
In seven seasons, Roethlisberger has many individual accomplishments that are record performances in Steelers history.<ref name="pro-football-reference.com">[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/teams/pit/career-passing.htm "Pittsburgh Steelers Career Passing Register"], Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref><ref>[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/teams/pit/single-season-passing.htm "Pittsburgh Steelers Single-season Passing Register"], Pro-Football-Reference.com</ref>

